From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Remove DNS resolver information leak

Detection vector: DNS-over-HTTPS or DNS-over-TLS client fingerprinting
identifies the resolver implementation by the query patterns, EDNS
options, and fallback behavior. The DoH provider selection also leaks
the user's configured provider.

This patch normalizes DNS query behavior to match Chrome's default
resolver pattern.

Surface: network-dns
Closes: DNS resolver fingerprinting

--- a/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc
+++ b/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void DNSTransaction::StartQuery() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: normalize EDNS0 options to match Chrome's default
+  // resolver behavior. Remove custom options that could identify this
+  // as a non-standard build.
